Euphorbia bicolor is a species of flowering plant in the family Euphorbiaceae.
It is a herbaceous perennial plant that typically grows to about 30 cm in height.
The leaves of Euphorbia bicolor are oblong, bright green in color, and have a smooth texture.
The flowers of Euphorbia bicolor are small and yellow-green in color, and are arranged in umbels.
The stems of Euphorbia bicolor are green, cylindrical, and covered in small bumps or tubercles.
It is commonly found in rocky areas, dry slopes, and desert landscapes in southwestern North America.
Euphorbia bicolor is often used in landscaping and xeriscaping due to its low maintenance requirements and unique visual characteristics.
